{"artefact":[["_response_info",{"status":"ok"}],["title","Access to Work"],["id","https://contentapi.production.alphagov.co.uk/access-to-work.json"],["web_url","https://www.gov.uk/access-to-work"],["format","programme"],["details",{"need_id":"1045","business_proposition":false,"alternative_title":"","overview":"Access to Work - money to help you when a disability or health condition affects the way you do your job - what you'll get, eligibility, apply","updated_at":"2012-10-05T13:08:10+00:00","parts":[{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/access-to-work/overview","slug":"overview","order":1,"title":"Overview","body":"<p>An Access to Work grant is money to help you find work or stay in a job. It&rsquo;s for people with a disability, health or mental health condition. </p>\n\n<p>The money you get can pay for things like: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>specialist equipment </li>\n  <li>travel when you can&rsquo;t use public transport</li>\n  <li>a communicator at a job interview </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>How much you get depends on your circumstances. It&rsquo;s only available in England, Scotland and Wales.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>Any money you get doesn\u2019t have to be paid back and won\u2019t affect your other benefits.</p>\n</div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/access-to-work/what-youll-get","slug":"what-youll-get","order":2,"title":"What you'll get","body":"<p>There is no set amount for an Access to Work grant. How much you get depends on your circumstances. </p>\n\n<p>The money can pay for things like: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>adaptations to the equipment you use</li>\n  <li>special equipment</li>\n  <li>a support worker or job coach to help you in your workplace</li>\n  <li>fares to work if you&rsquo;re unable to use public transport</li>\n  <li>disability awareness training for your colleagues</li>\n  <li>a communicator at a job interview</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>How you&rsquo;re paid</h2>\n\n<p>All benefits, pensions and allowances can be <a href=\"/how-to-have-your-benefits-paid\" title=\"How you're paid\">paid into an account</a>, eg a bank account. </p>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/access-to-work/eligibility","slug":"eligibility","order":3,"title":"Eligibility","body":"\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>Access to work is available to people in England, Scotland and Wales.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>You must be 16 or over and either: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>in a paid job or self-employed - you can&rsquo;t get it for voluntary work</li>\n  <li>unemployed and about to start a job or a work trial</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Your condition</h2>\n\n<p>Your disability or health condition must affect your ability to do a job or mean you have to pay work-related costs. For example, special computer equipment or travel costs because you can&rsquo;t use public transport. </p>\n\n<p>Your mental health condition must affect your ability to a job and means you need support to:  </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>start a new job</li>\n  <li>reduce absence from work  </li>\n  <li>stay in work </li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Exceptions</h2>\n\n<p>You may not qualify if you get any of these benefits:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Incapacity Benefit</li>\n  <li>Employment and Support Allowance</li>\n  <li>Severe Disablement Allowance</li>\n  <li>Income Support</li>\n  <li>National Insurance Credits</li>\n</ul>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/access-to-work/how-to-claim","slug":"how-to-claim","order":4,"title":"How to claim","body":"<p>To apply and find out what you can get, contact your regional Access to Work centre. </p>\n\n<table>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th>Where you live</th>\n      <th>Your regional centre</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>South East England, London, East of England</td>\n      <td>London</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>South West England, Wales, West Midlands, East Midlands</td>\n      <td>Cardiff</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Scotland, North West England, North East England, Yorkshire and Humberside</td>\n      <td>Glasgow</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h2>London</h2>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Access to Work - London</strong><br />\nTelephone: 020 8426 3110<br />\nTextphone: 020 8426 3133<br />\nFax: 020 8426 3134<br />\n<a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#097;&#116;&#119;&#111;&#115;&#117;&#046;&#108;&#111;&#110;&#100;&#111;&#110;&#064;&#106;&#111;&#098;&#099;&#101;&#110;&#116;&#114;&#101;&#112;&#108;&#117;&#115;&#046;&#103;&#115;&#105;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#097;&#116;&#119;&#111;&#115;&#117;&#046;&#108;&#111;&#110;&#100;&#111;&#110;&#064;&#106;&#111;&#098;&#099;&#101;&#110;&#116;&#114;&#101;&#112;&#108;&#117;&#115;&#046;&#103;&#115;&#105;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\nJobcentre Plus\n<br />Access to Work Operational Support Unit\n<br />Nine Elms Lane\n<br />London\n<br />SW95 9BH\n<br />\n</p></div></div>\n\n<h2>Cardiff</h2>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Access to Work - Cardiff</strong><br />\nTelephone: 02920 423 291<br />\nTextphone: 02920 644 886<br />\nFax: 02920 423 342<br />\n<a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#097;&#116;&#119;&#111;&#115;&#117;&#046;&#099;&#097;&#114;&#100;&#105;&#102;&#102;&#064;&#106;&#111;&#098;&#099;&#101;&#110;&#116;&#114;&#101;&#112;&#108;&#117;&#115;&#046;&#103;&#115;&#105;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#097;&#116;&#119;&#111;&#115;&#117;&#046;&#099;&#097;&#114;&#100;&#105;&#102;&#102;&#064;&#106;&#111;&#098;&#099;&#101;&#110;&#116;&#114;&#101;&#112;&#108;&#117;&#115;&#046;&#103;&#115;&#105;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\nJobcentre Plus\n<br />Access to Work Operational Support Unit\n<br />Alexandra House\n<br />377 Cowbridge Road East\n<br />Cardiff CF5 1WU\n<br />\n</p></div></div>\n\n<h2>Glasgow</h2>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Access to Work - Glasgow</strong><br />\nTelephone: 0141 950 5327<br />\nTextphone: 0845 6025850<br />\nFax: 0141 950 5265<br />\n<a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#097;&#116;&#119;&#111;&#115;&#117;&#046;&#103;&#108;&#097;&#115;&#103;&#111;&#119;&#064;&#106;&#111;&#098;&#099;&#101;&#110;&#116;&#114;&#101;&#112;&#108;&#117;&#115;&#046;&#103;&#115;&#105;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#097;&#116;&#119;&#111;&#115;&#117;&#046;&#103;&#108;&#097;&#115;&#103;&#111;&#119;&#064;&#106;&#111;&#098;&#099;&#101;&#110;&#116;&#114;&#101;&#112;&#108;&#117;&#115;&#046;&#103;&#115;&#105;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\nJobcentre Plus\n<br />Access to Work Operational Support Unit\n<br />Anniesland JCP\n<br />Baird Street\n<br />Glasgow G90 8AN\n<br />\n</p></div></div>\n\n<h2>Appeal a decision</h2>\n\n<p>You can appeal the decision about your Access to Work grant if you&rsquo;re unhappy with it. </p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.direct.gov.uk/prod_consum_dg/groups/dg_digitalassets/@dg/@en/@benefits/documents/digitalasset/dg_201702.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Appeal against a benefit decision (leaflet GL24)' (PDF, 5000KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download \u2018Appeal against a benefit decision (leaflet GL24)\u2019 (PDF, 5000KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/access-to-work/further-information","slug":"further-information","order":5,"title":"Further information","body":"\n"}]}],["tags",[{"title":"Finding a job","id":"https://contentapi.production.alphagov.co.uk/tags/working%2Ffinding-job.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes job search, volunteering, apprenticeships and job offers","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://contentapi.production.alphagov.co.uk/with_tag.json?tag=working%2Ffinding-job","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/working/finding-job"},"parent":{"title":"Working, jobs and pensions","id":"https://con